            'gid' => 'date-your-way-to-a-better-relationship',
            'name' => 'Date Your Way to a Better Relationship',
            'annotation' => 'Put the spark back in your date nights',
            'content' => '<blockquote><p>Creative couples dates to add some spark to your weekends</p></blockquote><p><a href="http://www.ayi.com/dating-blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/shutterstock_106006154-e1382454591720.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-2706" alt="Date Your Way to a Better Relationship" src="http://www.ayi.com/dating-blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/shutterstock_106006154-e1382454591720.jpg" width="636" height="330" /></a></p><p>Friday night, rent a video. Saturday night, rent a video. Sunday night, rent…well you know where this is going. Often, when in a long-term relationship, date nights become mundane and predictable. Put the spark back into your relationship. <strong>It’s easier than you think, but you will need to talk with your partner first.</strong> This really won’t take all that long and once it’s done all that’s left is to go out and have some fun.</p><p><em><strong>Related: <a title="Turn Your Apartment Into a Love Den" href="http://www.ayi.com/dating-blog/5-ways-to-turn-your-apartment-into-a-love-den/" target="_blank">5 Ways to Turn Your Apartment Into a Love Den</a></strong></em></p><h2>Creative Dates Add Spark to Your Relationship</h2><p><span>♥</span>Do you have similar hobbies or activities you enjoy? Plan a date around that. <a href="http://lifebytesbook.com/the-art-of-date-planning/">Talk with your partner </a>about things you may like to do. If you’re both athletic, go on a hiking date or have a date working out together at the gym, followed by a nice healthy snack at the gym&#8217;s café.</p><p><span>♥</span>Do you have <a title="Dating Outside Your Religion" href="http://www.ayi.com/dating-blog/online-dating-first-date-religious-beliefs-date-outside-faith/" target="_blank">vastly different interests</a>? Take turns planning dates that will introduce your partner to your hobby or fun activity.  His or her “thing” may never actually become <em>your</em> thing but you’ll at least have a better insight into what they find enjoyable.</p><h2>Do New Things Together</h2><p><span>♥</span>Do you <em>really</em> like doing the same old thing every week? You can still turn that up a notch or two. When I was growing up my parents had a date night every Saturday and they always went out to dinner. However, they made it a point to always go to a different restaurant, so they were continually trying different types of eateries.</p><p><span>♥</span><strong>No matter which route you choose, the key here is to be creative and have a sense of adventure.</strong> If you make the planning of your weekly date night a regular activity too you may find yourselves having as much fun in planning as in doing!</p><p><em><strong><em><strong>Related: <a title="Fall Date Ideas" href="http://www.ayi.com/dating-blog/dating-fall-date-ideas-slideshow/" target="_blank">6 Phenomenal Fall Date Ideas</a></strong></em></strong></em></p><p><strong><em><span>♥</span> Keep up with AYI’s latest trending reports, dating data and tips on <a href="http://bit.ly/19HI3uk">Twitter</a>, <a href="http://bit.ly/17lu9KZ">YouTube</a>, <a title="AYI on Pinterest" href="http://pinterest.com/ayi/" target="_blank">Pinterest</a> and <a title="AYI.com Dating Blog" href="http://www.ayi.com/dating-blog" target="_blank">our blog</a>. </em></strong></p><p><strong><em><span>♥</span> To <a title="AYI.com" href="http://ayitrk.com/?a=10026&amp;c=23&amp;s1=zoopa" target="_blank">browse singles</a> with similar interests in your area, visit <a title="AYI.com" href="http://ayitrk.com/?a=10026&amp;c=23&amp;s1=zoopa" target="_blank">AYI.com</a>.</em></strong></p>',
